**Prophet** | Extra Elected | Haunted
__Basics__
The Prophet may perform a miracle of resurrection and a miracle of protection once each.
__Details__
The Prophet is a replacement for the Guardian in *haunting* games and is elected on the first full day with a living Mayor and Gravekeeper, but no living Prophet.
During the night the prophet can perform a miracle of resurrection or a miracle of protection, but only one at a time.
The Prophet can perform each miracle once each. These limitations carry on to future elected Prophets.
The miracle of protection can protect one player from dying to all attacks that night.
The miracle of resurrection can turn one ghost player back into a living player.
Both miracles are end night actions but before attacks and banishes.
Miracles are announced in story time.
__Simplified__
The Prophet may perform a miracle of resurrection and a miracle of protection once each. It can do so during night but only one at a time.
They are both end night actions that are announced in story time.
The Prophet is elected  on the first full day with a living Mayor and Gravekeeper, but no living Prophet.
__Formalized__
__Card__
The Prophet performs miracles for all its followers to see.
